Use strongest domino for which there are many with that many spots in hand
maxSpots : function to count the most frequent number of spots
stepBack:
Given a Board, figure out what was played last turn and 'undo' that move
filter hand by this and get hsd
First Move:
If (5,4) in hand, use that
Target59:
Use domino which will give exactly 59 if in range
Target61:
Use domino which will give exactly 61 if in range
Target:
Use domino which will give the exact score desired
Check history for two consecutive turns played by the current player
Strongest Move:

Use scoreN with the resultant boards to figure out their most damaging potential plays
Use search with guessDomsInPlay as the opponent's hand to guess the most likely outcomes
checkKnocking:
Figure out, using History, what the opponent is knocking on
Both ends in the first of those turns will be what the opponent is knocking on
guessDomsInPlay:
guess what's in play using everything not on the board or in the hand
filter by checkKnocking
use guessDomsInPlay/checkKnocking to deny them a turn by playing something they can't respond to
hsdPlayer:
